                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3gt5g225/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>from ship to ship at <placeName>Havana</placeName>. And then<lb/> on my arrival here\n                I had fresh difficulties<lb/> to encounter before I could get possession<lb/> of it.\n                I say nothing about some three or four<lb/> dollars very unnecessary expenses\n                incurred and<lb/> which I had to pay out of my pocket. I had<lb/> quite enough to\n                see to in leaving <placeName>N York</placeName> without<lb/> at the very least\n                moment being worried about<lb/> a box of silver which if received here now\n                would<lb/> be in plenty of time.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I speak as I do about this affair for<lb/> your sake &amp; to show\n                you how seriously you<lb/> may inconvenience a friend by not properly<lb/>\n                considering his entire situation. <persName>Alexander</persName> will<lb/> tell you\n                how unhandsomely <persName>Adams &amp; Co</persName> behaved.<lb/> They performed\n                but a very small part of their contract<lb/> with you. By the by—Did you pay them\n                for taking the<lb/> box to <placeName>NY</placeName>. They said you had not &amp;\n                made me pay 14/—&amp;<lb/> then they would not send it on board.\n                    <persName>Alexander</persName> attended<lb/> to getting it &amp; had to bring it\n                to the vessel on the back of a carriage<lb/> about ½ hour before we left, &amp; the\n                job we had to set it<lb/> on board only was enough to set one crazy.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your shipment to <persName>Mr Touro</persName> is all right<lb/> we\n                have all the Bill Loding<add>?</add> calls for &amp; the keys also from<lb/> the\n                captain. <persName>Mr Touro</persName> told me a day or two ago that<lb/> he would\n                soon reply to your letter, which I read. I presume<lb/> he has done so. I forget the\n                date of it. We have not<lb/> opened any of the boxes as yet, but will very soon—</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3gt5g225/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
