              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3gt5g225/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">With regard to a Minister the Consecration &amp;c—<lb/> We have\n                written to <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> offering him<lb/> $25.00. He must be here\n                by the <date>1st</date> proximo or else<lb/> he will decline. If he comes he will\n                only remain<lb/> till <date>20th Jany</date>, then return to\n                    <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> &amp; be<lb/> here again before\n                    “<date>Sehbuot</date>” so he said in his letter<lb/> to me recd shortly after my\n                arrival here. The<lb/> congregation do not want the consecration to take<lb/> place\n                until we have a resident minister. I would<lb/> prefer otherwise particularly if it\n                could be say middle<lb/> of <date>Jany</date> when you could be here; but I can\n                not<lb/> say what they will do. From the <sic>tener</sic> of your last letter<lb/>\n                to <persName>Mr Touro</persName> I hope he will ask you to come, or that he<lb/>\n                will say to me that he will pay your expenses. If he does<lb/> I will do the rest\n                between my congr &amp; yours to secure your<lb/> presence here. I have done you the\n                fullest justice in the<lb/> sight of <persName>Mr. T</persName> &amp; also in that\n                of the congregation <add>?</add><lb/> they say “I swear by your name”. So you see if\n                I have any<lb/> complaints to make against you (as in the first part of this<lb/>\n                letter) I make them to <hi rend=\"underline\">you only</hi>. That is my system.—</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The German congr have sent a proposal<lb/> of $1500 to <persName>Mr\n                    Gutheim</persName> &amp; I have little doubt that<lb/> he will accept &amp; they\n                will have the man that ought to<lb/> have been here now performing the services for\n                us. I shall<lb/> not be in the least surprised if <persName>Mr. Nathan</persName>\n                does not<lb/> come after all &amp; then “we will be in a boat”. Alas.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I hope you are getting along better with your flock.<lb/> I fear\n                they (or some of them) will not appreciate you<lb/> until they lose you or come very\n                near it. Such is pure human nature.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3gt5g225/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
